I can get down with a critique of the usage of D-Class throughout the site's history, but the actual execution of this piece isn't particularly convincing me. The non-clinical, comedically slanted documentation feels extremely bog-standard and doesn't differentiate itself that well from the many other joke SCPs with that specific quirk, and the dialogue just failed to surprise me all that much, and often felt way too on-the-nose in its satire for my liking (Polk's long paragraph at the end exemplifies this for me).

Overall, there just isn't anything all that new or exceptional about how it was executed, and as such this didn't get much of a reaction out of me.

